reffering to "how an algorithm detect the human and what are the features it can extract to detect?"

    Detecting human beings accurately in a visual surveillance system is crucial for diverse application areas including abnormal event detection, human gait characterization,
   congestion analysis, person identification, gender classification and fall detection for elderly people. The first step of the detection process is to 
   detect an object which is in motion. Object detection could be performed using background subtraction, optical flow and spatio-temporal filtering techniques.
   
